crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a Remote Access Trojan (RAT) that provides a reverse shell. It establishes a connection to a command and control (C2) server, using a custom RC4-like algorithm (`_xcrypt`) to encrypt communications. Upon connection, it forks and executes `/bin/sh` via `_execve`, redirecting its I/O through a pseudo-terminal (`_posix_openpt`) to the C2 server. This grants the attacker interactive shell access. The malware also supports various backdoor commands, including file upload/download (`_proc_upload`, `_proc_download`), directory listing (`_proc_dir`), and file deletion (`_proc_rmfile`).
